<subSubSection pageId="179" pageNumber="180" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="179.[189,310,1098,1124]" box="[189,310,1098,1124]" pageId="179" pageNumber="180">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1098,1124]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="179" pageNumber="180" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1098,1124]" pageId="179" pageNumber="180">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="179.[189,1398,1145,1383]" pageId="179" pageNumber="180">
Externally, the new species is very similar in coloration to 
<taxonomicName authority="Distant, 1910" authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1910" box="[892,1219,1145,1171]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Drabescus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="179" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="natalensis">
<emphasis box="[892,1048,1145,1171]" italics="true" pageId="179" pageNumber="180">D. natalensis</emphasis>
Distant, 1910
</taxonomicName>
, the only other known African species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1870" box="[521,646,1180,1206]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Drabescus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="179" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[521,646,1180,1206]" italics="true" pageId="179" pageNumber="180">Drabescus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It can be distinguished from that species by the following characters: crown not as strongly produced, coloration of crown not as mottled, style apophysis spatulate (digitate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1910" box="[329,448,1251,1277]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Drabescus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="179" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="natalensis">
<emphasis box="[329,448,1251,1277]" italics="true" pageId="179" pageNumber="180">natalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), aedeagus with pair of long processes arising from ventral margin (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1910" box="[1279,1398,1251,1277]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Drabescus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="179" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="natalensis">
<emphasis box="[1279,1398,1251,1277]" italics="true" pageId="179" pageNumber="180">natalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with pair of short apical processes), and segment X with pair of long filamentous setae arising from ventral margin (absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1910" box="[506,625,1321,1347]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Drabescus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="179" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="natalensis">
<emphasis box="[506,625,1321,1347]" italics="true" pageId="179" pageNumber="180">natalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The 
<typeStatus box="[709,812,1321,1347]" pageId="179" pageNumber="180">holotype</typeStatus>
was compared with specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1910" box="[1240,1398,1321,1347]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Drabescus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="179" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="natalensis">
<emphasis box="[1240,1398,1321,1347]" italics="true" pageId="179" pageNumber="180">D. natalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which were collected at the same locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="179" pageNumber="180" type="etymology">
